Sasalin spewed a jet of flame, the towering Slakian igniting a small patch of forest before circling overhead, watching for the right moment. Strangely, when he slowed down, the eerie screeching behind him also stopped. Sasalin forgot that there was a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tenok, you've turned into a Slakian before!"
"Flying on your own and suddenly being dragged away by a huge pink dragon are two different things!"
"Alright, Kayer?"
Kayer clearly disagreed with Nishi's statement; he looked paler than usual, and his claws had dug deeply into Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slakian, but Sasalin obviously didn't care. That said, Sasalin realized he had scared his new friend and decided to find an open area to land.
"Sorry, sorry, I smelled something. I need to deal with it!"
"Did you really have to drag us along too?" Tenuk climbed down from Sasalin's back, sliding down his tail to the ground, and asked sharply. "We left Retvik behind! We abandoned that strong, aggressive brute! How is he ever going to find us?"
"He'll figure it out...," Nishi muttered in agreement. "Retvik may be slow, but he's not stupid."
"Can Retvik drive a car?"
Nishi blinked and turned to look at Tenuk. "Of course he can drive a car."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayer's. He started taking the bus to work purely because you always drove us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin suddenly burst into uncontrollable laughter, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took Sasalin a while before he could calm down.
"Sorry, sorry, I just imagined it—your big, armored friend riding a little bicycle designed for Temson children. That's so ridiculous! I wish I had telepathy. That idea is so funny! I definitely need to remember it!"
Kayer laughed too, because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. "Well, well. But what exactly did you smell? Why did you have to fly so fast?"
Sasalin snorted, took off quickly, and soon disappeared, then flew back and dropped a corpse in front of Nishi. It was an Orotharax, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one dead. I heard their screams. Smelled their blood. I must protect them, hunt down the killer. It is Isini's will. Those creatures are nearby."
The towering Slakian suddenly froze. Nishi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the clearing. A huge, pitch-black creature was staring at them, hissing. The thing suddenly spread its two pairs of massive wings and charged forward, directly at Sasalin, completely ignoring the three small figures standing between it and Sasalin. Kayer and Tenuk barely managed to dodge to the side, but Nishi found herself thrown to the ground, nearly knocked into Sasalin.
Sasalin grabbed Nishi by the arm, flung her onto his back with his long and nimble tail, and took off into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly gave chase.
Kayer muttered, drew a rifle from behind, and opened the bag, taking out a belt of bullets. He fastened the belt across his chest for easy access, but quickly realized that Nishi, Sasalin, and the monster were gone.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"Do you want to go after them?"
"Ridiculous."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? This rifle in my hands is powerful, and I can fire anytime. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to give himself some space. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, his arms transforming into wings. He soon became an ordinary light blue Slakian, but his eyes remained red.
"Come on up."
Tenuk now looked like an ordinary Slakian, with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of spikes growing for Kayer to grip. It took Tenuk a long time to take off, but once airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction and struggled to catch up.
However, Tenuk and Kayer quickly realized they were not facing only one opponent. A second dark monster surged up from below, and Tenuk barely avoided the impact.
"I guess this is the other terrifying big monster that Ranelux was worried about?" Kayer furrowed his brow and tried to shoot at the second monster but missed, quickly reloading his weapon.
Tenuk didn't respond; he was busy flying toward Nishi and Sasalin, even though another monster was chasing them. Kayer awkwardly turned around to face the creature. As the monster pursued them, Kayer considered it good news because it made him easier to aim and shoot at. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it howled in pain before disappearing into the woods. Kayer wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he felt confident it couldn't keep up.
Ahead, Sasalin was wildly flailing his body, spitting flames at the black monster, while Nishi desperately clung to him to avoid falling. Although the monster was surely injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs apparently hadn't caused too much damage. After Sasalin steadied himself, Nishi seized the opportunity to pull out her weapon—a shotgun she trusted. Of course, a shotgun couldn't take down a creature like this, but the scattered bullets might at least scare off the black beast?
